  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1080 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve and peel @red onion{1}. Finely chop one half; very thinly slice other half from pole to pole. Core, seed, and finely chop @poblano pepper{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/2%ounce}. Core and dice @roma tomatoes{2}. Halve @lime{1}; cut one half into wedges for serving.

Add sliced onion, @white wine vinegar{2%tbsp}, @sugar{2%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @water{1%tbsp} to a #medium bowl{}. Toss until sugar and salt are mostly dissolved. Set aside to marinate, tossing occasionally.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{20%ounce}, breaking up meat into pieces. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} using a #slotted spoon{}. Pour out and discard any excess grease in pan.

Heat another large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add chopped onion and poblano. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Return pork to pan and add @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp}, @tomato paste{2%tbsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @water{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until everything comes together in a saucy mixture, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} in a #small bowl{}. Stir in a splash or two of water to give crema a drizzly consistency. Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{12} in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave on high until warm, about ~{30%seconds}.

Divide filling, tomatoes, @monterey jack cheese{1/2%cup}, cilantro, pickled onion, and crema between tortillas.

> TIP: You can put everything in individual serving bowls and let everyone assemble their own tacos.

Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.